(Abstract: AbstractOsimertinib is an irreversible, third-generation epidermal growth factor) Tj
T*
(receptor \(EGFR\) tyrosine kinase inhibitor that is highly selective for EGFR-activating) Tj
T*
(mutations as well as the EGFR T790M mutation in patients with advanced non-small cell lung) Tj
T*
(cancer \(NSCLC\) with EGFR oncogene addiction. Despite the documented efficacy of osimertinib in) Tj
T*
(first- and second-line settings, patients inevitably develop resistance, with no further) Tj
T*
(clear-cut therapeutic options to date other than chemotherapy and locally ablative therapy for) Tj
T*
(selected individuals. On account of the high degree of tumour heterogeneity and adaptive) Tj
T*
(cellular signalling pathways in NSCLC, the acquired osimertinib resistance is highly) Tj
T*
(heterogeneous, encompassing EGFR-dependent as well as EGFR-independent mechanisms.) Tj
T*
(Furthermore, data from repeat plasma genotyping analyses have highlighted differences in the) Tj
T*
(frequency and preponderance of resistance mechanisms when osimertinib is administered in a) Tj
T*
(front-line versus second-line setting, underlying the discrepancies in selection pressure and) Tj
T*
(clonal evolution. This review summarises the molecular mechanisms of resistance to osimertinib) Tj
T*
(in patients with advanced EGF...) Tj
